since NFS mounted run dirs seems like it's the odd case out, maybe we should go back to putting that behind a flag and drop the safe_* stuff since it seems to cause trouble?  people running on NFS can set that?  at least DONT_RESET_PERMISSIONS is a clear flag...

Patch Set 1:

@Ian - sure. I have just been looking for a way to fix this.

So, solution would be to pull out safe_* operations, and have a DONT_RESET_PERMISSIONS flag?

or we can do both, if people prefer - i just want to get it fixed :)

Patch Set 1:

my preference is always less code :)  might want to check with dtroyer on his thoughts, as it seems he put all this in
